==Alternative spellings==
:'''Handheld''': Hand-held.
==Etymology==
Compound of English ''hand'' (see [[hand]]) + English ''held'' (see [[held]]; past participle of [[hold]])

==[[Adjective]]==

Small and light enough to be operated while you hold it in your hands.

==[[Noun]]==

A computing device (e.g. [[organizer]], Internet-enabled cell phone) that is operated while held in the hands.